UID:pAxuSl7azQXeZDXPqNP2w
SUMMARY:Earth Day Forest Bathing in the Garden
DTSTAMP:20260411T111907Z
DTSTART:20260422T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught by Deborah Wilk. Celebrate Earth Day with a mindful Fore
	st Bathing walk in the vibrant spring garden. Slow down\, breathe deep\, a
	nd open your senses with wonder as you deepen your connection to nature. S
	tep away from the stressors of the outside world\, as we restore mind\, bo
	dy and spirit while honoring our interdependence with the living world tha
	t surrounds and holds us\, fostering a sense of gratitude and stewardship 
	for the planet we call Home. \n\nDeborah Wilk\, psychotherapist and co-fou
	nder of Mindful in the Wild\, will guide you in practices that integrate m
	indfulness meditation and shinrin-yoku \\(Japanese Forest Bathing\\). The 
	walk is approximately one mile and will be on trails with various surfaces
	\, including some gentle inclines down to the more forested areas of the g
	arden.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-day-forest-b
	athing-in-the-garden/18185401/2026-04-22T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community &
	 Civic
