SUMMARY:Housing Justice Art Hang
DTSTAMP:20260411T111907Z
DTSTART:20260426T110000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join the Housing Justice Workgroup for an outing at the Frye Ar
	t Museum. This event is open to all DSA members\\\, whether you’re part of
	 the housing justice workgroup or just looking to connect with comrades an
	d enjoy the art exhibits. \\nWe’ll gather from 11:00–11:15 AM in the Frye 
	Parlor (just outside the café) before heading into the galleries together 
	to explore\\\, connect\\\, and reflect on art through a shared lens of jus
	tice and solidarity. Join us then\\\, or drop in anytime between 11:00 AM 
	and 1:00 PM and come find us in the galleries! \\n✨ The first 15 DSA membe
	rs to arrive will receive a DSA pin featuring our new logo. If you’re comf
	ortable doing so\\\, we’ll ask you to wear it so others can easily spot th
	e group as we move through the museum. Admission is free but we encourage 
	you to make a donation to support the museum if you’re able. \\nPublic str
	eet parking is available and free on Sundays along Terry Ave\\\, 9th Ave\\
	\, Columbia St\\\, Marion St\\\, and Cherry St.  \\nFor public transit opt
	ions\\\, accessibility details\\\, and museum policies\\\, please visit th
	e Frye Art Museum website: https://fryemuseum.org. Bring a friend (or two)
	!\n\nhttps://seattledsa.org/event/housing-justice-art-hang/\n\nFrom Seattl
	e DSA
URL:https://seattledsa.org/event/housing-justice-art-hang/
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\\\, 704 Terry Ave\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98104\\\,
	 United States
